---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="For Developers" description="Integrate your energy generation assets with the SynergyCarbon PoVC platform. Deploy witness nodes and start minting verified credits.">

  <header class="page-hero">
    <h1>For Project Developers</h1>
    <p>
      Deploy witness hardware, select methodologies, and start minting
      verified carbon credits from your energy assets.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- Onboarding Timeline -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Onboarding Timeline</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      From registration to live minting in under 30 days.
    </p>

    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item reveal delay-1">
        <div class="timeline-dot">1</div>
        <h3>Register &amp; Authenticate</h3>
        <p>
          Complete SPARK visual challenge authentication. Receive your ML-DSA-87
          key pair, tenant ID, and console credentials. Configure branding.yaml.
        </p>
        <span class="timeline-duration">Day 1</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item reveal delay-2">
        <div class="timeline-dot">2</div>
        <h3>Site Assessment</h3>
        <p>
          We evaluate your generation assets, sensor infrastructure, and connectivity.
          Optimal witness node placement and sampling configuration recommended.
        </p>
        <span class="timeline-duration">Day 2&ndash;5</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item reveal delay-3">
        <div class="timeline-dot">3</div>
        <h3>Deploy Witness Nodes</h3>
        <p>
          Install Universal Witness Node adapters at each generation site. Configure
          sensor endpoints (Modbus RTU/TCP, OPC-UA, or analog 4-20mA) and register
          nodes through governance.
        </p>
        <span class="timeline-duration">Week 1&ndash;2</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item reveal delay-4">
        <div class="timeline-dot">4</div>
        <h3>Select Methodology &amp; Validate</h3>
        <p>
          Choose from 7 pre-approved methodologies. Run validation attestations to
          confirm data quality. Establish quorum consensus across your witness network.
        </p>
        <span class="timeline-duration">Week 2&ndash;3</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item reveal delay-5">
        <div class="timeline-dot">5</div>
        <h3>Go Live</h3>
        <p>
          Credits mint automatically as attestations verify. Configure marketplace
          listings, forward contract terms, and automated retirement triggers.
        </p>
        <span class="timeline-duration">Week 4+</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Supported Energy Sources -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="section" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0;">
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Supported Energy Sources</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
        Five source types with optimized witness configurations and yield models.
      </p>

      <div class="detail-grid">
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
          <h3>Solar PV</h3>
          <p>
            Irradiance sensors + inverter output. Typical yield: 0.4&ndash;0.8 tCO&#8322;e/MWh
            depending on grid displacement factor. Supports fixed, tracking, and bifacial.
          </p>
          <span class="badge" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Est. $8&ndash;16/MWh revenue</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
          <h3>Wind</h3>
          <p>
            Turbine SCADA integration via OPC-UA. Yield: 0.3&ndash;0.7 tCO&#8322;e/MWh.
            Supports onshore and offshore, individual turbine or farm-level monitoring.
          </p>
          <span class="badge" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Est. $6&ndash;14/MWh revenue</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
          <h3>Biogas</h3>
          <p>
            Flow meters on digesters and generators. Yield: 0.5&ndash;1.2 tCO&#8322;e/MWh
            including methane capture credit. Landfill, agricultural, and wastewater.
          </p>
          <span class="badge" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Est. $10&ndash;24/MWh revenue</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-4">
          <h3>Thermoelectric (ThermogenZero)</h3>
          <p>
            TEG output monitoring via Modbus. Waste heat recovery from industrial
            processes. First customer integration with full deployment support.
          </p>
          <span class="badge" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Est. $12&ndash;28/MWh revenue</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-5">
          <h3>Carbon Capture &amp; Storage</h3>
          <p>
            CO&#8322; mass flow meters on capture trains. Direct measurement of captured
            tonnes. Supports post-combustion, pre-combustion, and direct air capture.
          </p>
          <span class="badge" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">Est. $50&ndash;120/tCO&#8322;e revenue</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Witness Node Deployment -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Witness Node Deployment</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      Universal hardware adapter for any energy generation site.
    </p>

    <div class="detail-grid">
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
        <h3>Hardware Requirements</h3>
        <p>
          ARM Cortex-M33 with secure enclave, tamper-evident housing, Ethernet
          or LTE-M connectivity. Power: 5W typical. Operating range: -40&deg;C to 85&deg;C.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
        <h3>Sensor Protocols</h3>
        <p>
          Modbus RTU (RS-485), Modbus TCP, OPC-UA, analog 4-20mA. Custom protocol
          adapters available through the SDK. Sampling rate: 1s to 60s configurable.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
        <h3>Security Model</h3>
        <p>
          ML-DSA-87 key generation on first boot. Keys stored in secure enclave,
          never exported. Firmware updates require signed packages. Anti-rollback protection.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Methodology Selection Guide -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="section" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0;">
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Methodology Selection Guide</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
        Match your source type to the optimal carbon accounting methodology.
      </p>

      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <table class="info-table reveal">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Source Type</th>
              <th>Recommended Methodology</th>
              <th>Registry</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Solar / Wind</td><td>CDM ACM0001</td><td>CDM, Verra VCS</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Biogas (landfill)</td><td>VCS AMS-III-H</td><td>Verra VCS</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Biogas (agricultural)</td><td>Gold Standard</td><td>Gold Standard</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Thermoelectric</td><td>EPA AP-42 + IPCC AR5</td><td>Verra VCS, ISCC</td></tr>
            <tr><td>CCS</td><td>CDM ACM0001 + IPCC AR5</td><td>CDM, Verra VCS</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section" style="text-align: center;">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Start Building</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      Explore the API, deploy your first witness node, or try the demo console.
    </p>
    <div class="reveal delay-2">
      <a href="/api" class="btn-primary" style="margin-right: 0.75rem;">API Reference</a>
      <a href="https://console.synergycarbon.io?demo=true" class="btn-outline" style="color: var(--sc-primary-dark); border-color: var(--sc-primary-dark);">Try Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
